            <!-- OVERVIEW & APPROACH GRID -->
            <div class="sections-grid">
              <!-- OVERVIEW -->
              <div class="service-section">
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>
                  Mastering is the final stage before distribution. It ensures your music
                  translates consistently across listening systems while preserving the
                  character and intent of the mix.
                </p>
                <p>
                  The goal is not to reshape the record, but to elevate and prepare it
                  for release with clarity, cohesion and technical precision.
                </p>
              </div>

              <!-- APPROACH -->
              <div class="service-section">
                <h2>Approach</h2>
                <p>
                  My approach to mastering is subtle and deliberate. I focus on tonal
                  balance, dynamic integrity and spatial depth while respecting the
                  emotional direction of the mix.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Decisions are guided by translation — how the record feels on studio
                  monitors, headphones, small speakers and larger systems. The objective
                  is consistency without sacrificing impact.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- DELIVERABLES & PRICING GRID -->
            <div class="sections-grid">
              <!-- DELIVERABLES -->
              <div class="service-section">
                <h2>Deliverables</h2>
                <ul>
                  <li>Stereo Masters (16/24bit WAV)</li>
                  <li>Sequencing and spacing for EPs or albums</li>
                  <li>DDP file for CD Printing</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <!-- ESTIMATED PRICING -->
              <div class="service-section">
                <h2>Pricing:<span style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0; text-transform: none; margin-left: 8px;">50–70€ per track</span></h2>
                <p>
                  Rates depend on track count and whether the project involves single
                  tracks or full releases.
                  Stem Mastering is also available for projects that require more detailed work on the mix elements.
                  <br>If you're unsure where your project fits, feel free to get in touch.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- BOOKING -->
